22 3-9-243. Winery private club permit — Scope — Restrictions.
23 (a) The Director of the Alcoholic Beverage Control Division may issue
24 a winery private club permit that authorizes the winery private club permit
25 holder to:
26 (1) Operate a winery private club and manufacture, produce, or
27 bottle one (1) or more varieties of wine, not to exceed ten thousand (10,000)
28 cases per year;
29 (2) Store wine manufactured, produced, or bottled by the winery
30 private club and other wine that the winery private club permit holder may
31 lawfully purchase from retailers or other wineries;
32 (3) Bottle on the premises wine that the winery private club
33 permittee has lawfully purchased in bulk from an out-of-state winery;
34 (4) Sell on the premises wine manufactured, produced, bottled,
35 or lawfully purchased by the winery private club for off-premises consumption
36 and for on-premises consumption during legal operating hours;
